Another alternative could be using regular expression. (**[Try it on Regex101](https://regex101.com/r/7leAKA/1)**)
`const regex = /(\d+)\[([A-Za-z]+)\]/g;`

The above regex will find a string pattern which match `number[letter]` like `3[a]`, `2[bc]`, etc.
For example, if full match the string part of `2[bc]`.
* The *1<sup>st</sup> Capturing Group* (**number**) is `2`
* The *2<sup>nd</sup> Capturing Group* (**letter**) is `bc`


Then, replace it with letter repeated number of times by using `letter.repeat(number)`. And now you can get the decode string of `bcbc`.

This is how I'm trying to do it:

```
var decodeString = function (s) {
  const regex = /(\d+)\[([A-Za-z]+)\]/g;

  function replacer(match, number, letter) {
    return letter.repeat(number);
  }

  while (s.includes('[')) {
    s = s.replace(regex, replacer);
  }
  return s;
};
```

