solutions.content:
We will solve the problem by dividing it into subproblems. The algorithm is as follows:

1. Iterate through the string
2. If we have a closing bracket, subproblem is done
3. If the current character is a letter, append it and continue
4. If the current character is an opening bracket, append it as count times
5. If none of the above, we have a digit that represents how many times we should append the subproblem. To accomplish it, don't forget that we may have digits which has more than one digit. So, if we see sequential digits, the previous one should be multiplied by 10 to calculate the count number.

```
class Solution {
    int i = 0; //tricky part, we globally iterate forward with the help of defining this variable as global

    public String decodeString(String s) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        int count = 0;

        while (i < s.length()) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);
            i++;

            if (c == ']') { //subproblem is done
                break;
            }

            if (Character.isLetter(c)) { //append and continue
                sb.append(c);
                continue;
            }

            if (c == '[') {
                String tmp = decodeString(s); //recursive call to solve the subproblem
                for (int j = 0; j < count; j++) {
                    sb.append(tmp);
                }
                count = 0; // reset the counter
            } else {
                count = count * 10 + c - '0'; //handle count case which has more than one digit
            }

        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```

