# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
use 1 stack to store the number of times the string has to be repeated and one to keep the letters of the string
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
use ] to indicate the end of the repeated part when encountered take the top most integer from the integer stack and the part to be repeated from the other stack. the repeated part will be until we have encountred [ this in stack. repeat the string. then store the string in ans string if stack is empty but if stack is not empty then that string is in another [] so it has to be repeated again so store it back in stack.  
