# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
continue to decode until a string has a number, store the number and the string in a vector.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Store The number and corresponding string in the vector, copy the string in i+1 to i number of times and return the string, continue if the resulting string has a number. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(depth of brackets)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

Upvote if you find it helpful vro ;)

